    <p> Back I got a forwarded mail from a Michael who explained to me in it that he would have deposited the key to the apartment at Fedex for professional reasons. Against the deposit, he would tell me the pick -up number and I could then pick up the keys from Fedex. </p>
    <p> Firstly, I have not seen a fedex in Australia and secondly I slowly became puzzled because the guy was first called Craig and now Michael suddenly. I wrote back that I would like to take a look at the apartment first and who he was now Craig or Michael. In response, I was now addressed with Michael and it would only be possible to visit the apartment if I would pay the deposit beforehand. Now it was finally clear to me that it would be fraud and decided on other rooms. </p>
    <h2 style="display:inline;"> No luck in the second attempt </h2>
    <p> Next I found an interesting room near my work. It was in a nice side street that reminded me a little of Spanish small towns. 2 floors with veranda and balcony. I really liked this room. Unfortunately I was not lucky in this case and someone else got the room. </p>
    <h2 style="display:inline;"> Someone lives in the living room </h2>
    <p> The third apartment was super located. With a great view towards Darling Harbor. With your own pool, fitness room and sauna in the basement. The whole thing only had two hooks. First, the rent was a good distance too high because I would live a room for two people alone. Second another roommate lives in the living room in an area separated with bed sheets. I found that stupid because the apartment has an open kitchen and you can't really prepare something in the evening. </p>
    <h2 style="display:inline;"> Backwards out </h2>
    <p> On the same evening I got the opportunity to look at another apartment. There it was about a fairly large room with direct access to the garden behind the house and your own bathroom. The whole thing even for a reasonably bearable price. So I went there in the evening. I liked the area quite well. It would really not be far from work. It didn't look that bad from the outside. But when the landlord opened me and I saw the kitchen and the unusable living room, I promptly went out again. On the other hand it was <a href="/de/reiseblog/2012/11/01/widerlich-balmain-backpackers.html"> Balmain Backpacker Hostel </a> yes clinically in. Well, thank you. I didn't want to get death or worse illnesses here. So just away quickly. </p>
