    <h2 style="display:inline;"> Finally something suitable </h2>
    <p> The next day I looked at two more apartments. The first was actually approved. However, there were once again several applicants and I also had the quiet hope for the second apartment because it is now almost in the backyard of my current office and secondly because the building is only a few years old. So I also went to the second apartment tour. It turned out that there was no living room here, but two more rooms were collected. </p>
    <p> One of them should become mine. And that with air conditioning and your own access to the very large balcony. The kitchen is new and modern. The bathroom? Oh well. Nothing that does not get clean with two bottles of champions and a certain muscle strength. Since the landlord even came towards me with the rental price, I struck and took the room. For German standards, it is still unthinkable. I live here with 6 other people in an apartment that is intended for 4 people and still pay $ 260 per week. This makes it more no more than &euro; 900 per month. </p>
    <p> But is still ok for the location. First, I have less than 3 minutes to work. Second, I only have about 5 minutes walk to the main train station and thirdly it is only 10 minutes to the city center. So I can do everything on foot here and don't always have to take the bus. </p>
    <p> The landlord then told me that some of the rooms will be released in the next few days/weeks if I might want to choose a bigger one. This should also include the large bedroom with its own bathroom and also own access to the balcony. But it was too expensive for me alone because this room is intended for two people. </p>
    <p> Who then moved in there? I'll come back on that later. Next time I will tell you more about my remaining days in the hostel. </p>
    <p> Greetings from Sydney. </p>
